<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-24T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1238</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-24T13:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>64. Department is seriously concerned over your 38 of November 15, 9 p.m.
                            Please report more fully in regard to proclamation of holy war of Islam
                            concerning which Department has no information.</p>
                        <p>Department cautions you against making any statements which could give
                            the impression that the United States was considering taking sides in
                            the present conflict, and desires you to maintain the policy of strict
                            neutrality which the Government of the United States has assumed in its
                            relations to the belligerent nations in all parts of the world.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>